reviews.review_text: sounds good phils gettin funky in bucket sound is good check it out

F*** the bucket There's waaaay more to this one than bucket, kid!!! Just check the vocal effects on the end of Fire. Whoa! Pass the Graffix!! This is a smoker!! A 16 minute Estimated?? And sound is real good!

Brentski Check out Brent on All Over Now...He is all over the place and the scat is nice also.. but don't stop there, the rest of the show is great too! Check out what Birdsgosouth said & check that shit out too..

'84 '84 is an underrated year.  They did some great shows, one of the last years they could get real spacey.  I think after '85 they really stopped jamming with the exception of fall tour '89.  I saw 13 of my 97 shows in '84, including the two Hampton nights.  These shows smoked.  Were any of you there also?

Hampton I saw both nights and this one was remarkably strong, especially for the opening night of a tour. I sort of half-agree with the statement that '84 was the last year they really got waaaaaay out there much....I have a lot of shows from the late 80s into maybe mid-'91 that I like as well, but they didn't jam with as much frequency.
hampton was heaven these were my 3rd  and 4th shows  amazing  a good time was had by all
Hampton ruled one of the top 10 of the 110+ shows I went to. Scarlet>Fire was amazing, the Dead always cranked it out in the spaceship.
4-13-84 Nice show! Excellent sound as per usual from Charlie.
Scarlet>Fire Best One I was at. First road show for me. One of the best 2nd sets of the 80's sound is Miller that's all you need to know

Houston..we have lift off~! Nice sound on this 84 beauty..Can't say that I like the Day Job opener..but what the hell, I'll let pass by..let pass by..The rest of the set tingles with pure energy right to the end..But what I really love from this show is the smoking Scarlet>Fire a must have or at least give it a listen..This show is up there with some of the better ones from 84..GIVE IT A WHIRL>Forever Grateful>Forever Dead~!!!!!!!

Friday the 13th-  tidewater camping 🦀🐟 Dodged the fuzz all day getting to the mothership. 
1st night spring tour -
💃🏽🕺🏻💃🏽🕺🏻🍄🌹

Electric Dance Music I was there and don’t remember it sounding this good. Blew off the first set due to set list. 

Scarlet>Fire is So Fat and Juicy ! You can hear everyone clearly, Phil is very active and threads all the parts together. Healy throws in some miniature paper pictures and stirs the pot... halfway through the jam Jerry’s shining and Brent starts dropping Marimba sounds into the mix, they work together to build the foundation for a Smokin’ Fire. The song crescendos with Healy using the echo pedal on the chorus. Loved it when he’d join the fun. 

Estimated is surprisingly strong for a tour opening show. If you’re familiar with the Lysergic Meltdown 10.14.84 in Hartford, this was the early precursor. 

Oh, did I mention the sound is nice and full?
